gui-speedtest (1.5.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Hotfix: 40×-100× speedup on networks with broken IPv6 transit.
    Root cause: DNS for hosts like speed.cloudflare.com returns IPv6
    addresses first; Python's urllib tries them in order and waits for
    the full socket timeout (~60s) per IPv6 address before falling back
    to IPv4. curl uses Happy Eyeballs (RFC 8305) to try both families
    in parallel, which masked the issue when comparing.
  * Fix: socket.getaddrinfo wrapper at module load reorders results to
    put IPv4 first. No effect on IPv6-only hosts (no v4 addresses ->
    v6 list is returned unchanged). No effect on IPv6-fast / IPv4-fast
    paths (IPv4 connects in <50ms like IPv6 would have).
  * Observed on user's Tuhin Enterprise ISP: Cloudflare connection_info
    30s -> 0.08s, latency 10065ms -> 53ms, 25MB download 62s -> 1.4s
    (141 Mbps). Ookla was unaffected because its CLI already uses IPv4
    by default.

 -- Mahmud Farooque <farooque7@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 17:00:00 +0600

