gui-speedtest (1.3.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Cancel UX: Cancel now produces instant UI feedback. v1.3.1's cancel
    path worked functionally (the worker thread exited correctly after
    socket shutdown) but the UI could stay on the old "Testing download…"
    text for many seconds on slow links because 40+ queued progress
    idle_adds were draining in front of the "Cancelling…" label update.
  * Fix: _cancel_test now updates UI synchronously from the click handler
    (we're on the main thread already) — status, progress text, button
    sensitivity flip instantly.
  * Fix: the download / upload / latency callbacks short-circuit on
    self.cancelled so already-in-flight progress events from the worker
    thread skip their UI updates on arrival. No more stale "0.6 Mbps"
    overwriting "Cancelling…".
  * Fix: _finish_run now dispatches at GLib.PRIORITY_HIGH so it preempts
    any remaining progress backlog. Also logs its entry — an absence of
    "_finish_run: cancelled=True" in the log now genuinely means it
    didn't run, not that it ran without logging.
  * Feature: "Clear" button in the log viewer (alongside Copy All).
    Truncates the current log file and drops rotated backups so the
    next run produces a clean trace.

