gui-speedtest (1.3.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * GUI: fix sparklines / ping histogram not rendering. On Ubuntu 26.04
    (resolute) and other distros that don't ship python3-gi-cairo as a
    transitive dep of python3-gi, Gtk.DrawingArea draw_func callbacks
    fail with "Couldn't find foreign struct converter for 'cairo.Context'"
    — silently, inside GTK's paint pipeline. The widget reserves space
    but nothing draws.
  * Root cause: pygobject needs python3-gi-cairo installed AND cairo
    imported somewhere in the process to register the foreign-struct
    converter between libcairo and Python cairo.Context objects.
  * Fix: add python3-gi-cairo to the .deb Depends, and `import cairo`
    at the top of gui_window.py so pip users also get the converter
    registered (assuming they have pycairo).

